                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d572">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/885d: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-23T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 23, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>547. We have stressed to the Iranian Legation here the points made in the final
                    paragraph of your 1007, October 19, 8 p.m. and we believe you should take
                    similar action with the Prime Minister as under instructions from the
                    Department.</p>
                <p>Sent to Tehran. Repeat to Moscow marked “For Jernegan”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
